    "summary": "I am a European and Dutch patent attorney with V.O. Patents & Trademarks. My daily practice is focused on global patent prosecution for inventions pertaining to chemistry and chemical engineering. I also handle opposition and appeal procedures before the EPO. My combined legal and technical background (LLM and MSc) enables me to clearly explain inventions to the patent offices while navigating complex patent procedures.\nIn addition, I am a co-author of Visser's Annotated European Patent Convention, one of the leading handbooks on European patent law. Contributing to the book requires me to stay up-to-date with the latest rules of the EPO, it also gives me more in-depth knowledge of European patent law.\nMy approach is straightforward and to-the-point while trying to secure the strongest protection for my client's technology. Inventions I've worked on include industrial chemical processes for fertilizer production, methods to make wood more durable (acetylation), polymer technology, 3D printing materials, and nanomaterials. ",
